{"questionId":"13356112","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Toktam walks to work on mornings when her car does not start and it is <strong>not</strong> raining. Toktam takes a taxi to work on mornings when her car does not start and it is raining.</p>\n<p>Where Toktam lives, there is a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math> probability of rain on any given morning, independent of any other morning. The probability of Toktam’s car starting is independent of the weather.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability that Toktam will <strong>not</strong> have to take a taxi in a particular workweek.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to find the probability of taking a taxi, (or <em>not</em> taking a taxi);&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math>(take taxi)<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>35</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>45</mn></math>&nbsp;,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math>(not take taxi)<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>65</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>35</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>55</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1575</mn></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8425</mn></math>&nbsp;seen&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>correct use of binomial distribution with their probability</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi><mo>~</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1575</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi><mo>~</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8425</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1575</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>5</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8425</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>5</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;seen&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>424</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>424472</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[4 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13356112","referenceCode":"23N.1.SL.TZ2.11b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the probability that Toktam will not have to take a taxi in a particular workweek.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":